    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-03T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-03T00:35:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/7–344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-03T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >July 3, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>474. Millspaugh informs me Prime Minister yesterday expressed to Majlis his
                    confidence United States Mission and supported Millspaugh proposal that question
                    of economic powers be allowed to rest 3 or 4 months to give time for results of
                    mission’s operations to become visible. Majority of Majlis was favorable and
                    Millspaugh regards immediate crisis as past and that he has won victory.</p>
                <p>In view of this classification [<hi rend="italic">clarification?</hi>] of status
                    of road transport directors am authorizing resumption of Lend Lease
                        deliveries.<note n="18" xml:id="d435fn18">The Chargé had temporarily held in
                        abeyance the delivery of unpaid for Lend-Lease goods then in Iran awaiting
                        delivery to the Iranian Government; he had taken this action on his own
                        initiative in connection with another matter involving technical
                        considerations and unrelated to policy matters.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
